metadata.description:
Sometimes we have to break down to BREAKTHROUGH...

And that’s what the BREAKTHROUGH collection is all about. We’ve all been in that cruel tug of war between our paralyzing fear of change, and our guilt of staying the same…

But with this project I want to remind you that change has its own timeline, and that you should keep believing in your own breakthrough…  

This collection is made up of my first two songs, and I want you to have a piece of them… of me. First up was 'BROKEN,' and now comes ‘FOOL’…

I wrote this song about my first heartbreak, but I know we’ve all felt the pain of being replaced and questioning where things went wrong. So this one is for all of us!

lyrics.text:
Every word you said 
Is like a tattoo
And when you said forever
I thought you meant it too

It’s funny how things change
When life gets in the way
Of all the million promises
Not a single one you kept

And now I wonder
Was I fool to think that
You were different too
And now I wonder
Was I a fool
To trust you with my heart and soul

And all the plans we had
And all the trips we’d take
And every kiss you gave me
Was all in vain
Still waiting for the call that never came

So easy to forget
So easy to replace me
You take her to the places 
You promised you would take me
I had to learn the hard way 
That you didn't deserve me

And I spent to many nights
Thinking to myself
What did I do wrong
Why you left me behind
Why you were not willing 
To fight for what we had

And now I wonder
Was I a fool
To trust you with my heart and soul

And all the plans we had
And all the trips we’d take
And every kiss you gave me
Was all in vain
Still waiting for the call that never came

Please look me in the eyes
One last time
And tell me baby please
It wasn’t all a lie
Please look me in the eyes
One last time
And when you said I love you 
You meant it, right?

Every word you said 
Is like a tattoo
And when you said forever
I thought you meant it too
